(* ---- 3.1 Overview of PREM ----                                *)
(*                                                              *)
(* The Preliminary Reference Earth Model (PREM) was published   *)
(* by Dziewonski & Anderson in 1981 and remains the standard    *)
(* 1-D reference model of the Earth's interior. It was           *)
(* constructed by inverting a massive dataset comprising:         *)
(*   - Free oscillation eigenfrequencies (normal modes)          *)
(*   - Surface wave dispersion measurements                      *)
(*   - Body wave travel times from the ISC bulletin              *)
(*   - Astronomical-geodetic constraints (mass, moment of        *)
(*     inertia)                                                  *)
(*                                                              *)
(* PREM specifies density rho(r), P-wave velocity alpha(r),     *)
(* S-wave velocity beta(r), and the quality factors Q_mu(r)     *)
(* and Q_kappa(r) as functions of radius. The model is           *)
(* piecewise-polynomial within each layer, with discontinuities  *)
(* at major boundaries:                                          *)
(*                                                              *)
(*   Inner Core Boundary (ICB): r = 1221.5 km (5150 km depth)   *)
(*   Core-Mantle Boundary (CMB): r = 3480 km (2891 km depth)    *)
(*   670-km discontinuity: r = 5701 km                          *)
(*   400-km discontinuity: r = 5971 km                          *)
(*   Mohorovicic discontinuity: r ~ 6346 km (24.4 km depth)     *)
(*                                                              *)
(* Our implementation tabulates the PREM values and uses         *)
(* Mathematica's Interpolation function within each continuous   *)
(* layer, respecting the discontinuities. This gives smooth      *)
(* velocity profiles that can be evaluated at any radius for     *)
(* the ray tracing calculations in Section 4.                   *)

(* Plot the P-wave and S-wave velocity profiles as functions of depth *)
plotPREMProfiles[]

(* Plot a cross-section of the Earth showing the internal layers *)
(* colored by P-wave velocity *)
plotPREMCrossSection[]


